                    <span>The adventures of Iwan Chonkin are a master piece of satyre! They even surpass Hasek's world famous adventures of the soldier Shwejk! But, of course, the Soviet Union in the time of Stalin was more absurd than the Habsburg Monarchy in the time of Hasek and Kafka!</span>
                  
              
